FBIS4-58589 "drnes087dd_94001" FBIS-NES-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 Palestinian Affairs 'Arafat Says Palestinians `Optimistic' About State 'Arafat Says Palestinians `Optimistic' About State JN0405182994 Paris Radio Monte Carlo in Arabic 1710 GMT 4 May 94 JN0405182994 Paris Radio Monte Carlo Arabic BFN [Interview with PLO Executive Committee Chairman Yasir 'Arafat by Faridah al-Shubashi in Cairo on 4 May -- recorded] [Text] [Al-Shubashi] Mr. President, on this day and after listening to your speech this morning, what do you have to say to your people in the occupied Palestinian territories, those who are optimistic or those who are pessimistic about the agreement? ['Arafat] The first thing I would like to emphasize is that our people are optimistic, our people, the people who forge miracles, the people of martyrs, the people of sacrifices, the people against whom the conspiracy has been since the turn of the century until now [words indistinct] different opinions. However, I do not believe that there are pessimists among our people. This is the people [words indistinct] the Koran describes by saying: In this land are a people of exceeding strength [Koranic verse] [Al-Shubashi] Mr. President, are you optimistic about the scope of the Palestinian state, God willing? ['Arafat] [Words indistinct] the Palestinian people have actively contributed to building many of the Arab countries. They have contributed to Arab civilization and have largely contributed with their blood, spirit, ideas, muscles, experience, aspirations and [word indistinct] in all the Arab walks of life. I am confident [words indistinct] soon and very soon. Today, we laid the corner stone for the edifice of this Palestinian state. They see it as something far off, and we see it as something near [word indistinct]. [Al-Shubashi] Mr. President, thank you.
